                        <i>Naja</i> : from Old Indian <i>naga</i>, meaning "snake";
                    </div>

                    <div class="info-box-paragraph">
                        <i>atra</i>: after the snake's color - the Latin term ater means "dark" or "black".
                    </div>
                    The Chinese name <span lang="zh-TW">眼鏡蛇</span> (yan3jing4she2) means "Spectacled Snake", referring to the markings on the back of the hood that resemble eyeglasses.
                </div>
            </div>
